TITLE: Using @deephaven/jsapi-shim in a React Component
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to import the dh object and PropTypes from the shim library. The component shows listening for session events and using the PropTypes for type checking.
SOURCE: https://github.com/deephaven/web-client-ui/blob/main/packages/jsapi-shim/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import dh, { PropTypes as APIPropTypes } from '@deephaven/jsapi-shim'

class MyComponent {
  componentDidMount() {
    const { session } = this.props;
    session.addEventListener(
      dh.IdeSession.EVENT_COMMANDSTARTED,
      event => {
        console.log('Command started event', event);
      }
    );
  }

  render() {
    return null;
  }
}

MyComponent.proptypes = {
  session: APIPropTypes.IdeSession.isRequired,
}

export default MyComponent;
```

